0:30:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58162</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Volleyball Secures Historic Victory Over No. 19 BYU</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2025/10/3/west-virginia-volleyball-secures-historic-victory-over-no-19-byu.aspx</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2025/10/3/west-virginia-volleyball-secures-historic-victory-over-no-19-byu.aspx</guid><category>Volleyball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Trinity Sheridan " src="https://wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/10/3/DSC00870.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University volleyball team (13–2, 1–2 Big 12) earned a landmark win on Friday night, defeating No. 19 BYU in a five-set thriller (26–24, 14–25, 25–23, 25–19, 15–12). This victory marks the program's fifth win against a ranked opponent in its history and the first-ever home win against a ranked team. It is also the first victory over a ranked opponent since 2021, when WVU swept then-No. 23 Michigan in the Navy Tournament. Additionally, it represents the Mountaineers' first triumph over BYU, having previously lost all four meetings in straight sets.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/3/DSC00870.jpg" /><media:content url="https://wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/3/DSC00870.jpg"><media:title>Trinity Sheridan </media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/3/DSC00870.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 3 Oct 2025 22:50:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>17</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58164</s:story_id></item><item><title>Countdown to Kickoff – Mountaineers to Play Some Late-Night Football in Provo, Utah, Tonight</title><l